            {'question_text': 'Two pipes A and B can fill a tank in 15 minutes and 20 minutes respectively. Both pipes are opened together but after 4 minutes, pipe A is turned off. What is the total time required to fill the tank?', 'option_a': '10 min 20 sec', 'option_b': '11 min 45 sec', 'option_c': '12 min 30 sec', 'option_d': '14 min 40 sec', 'correct_answer': 'D', 'explanation': 'Part filled in 4 min = 4(1/15 + 1/20) = 4(7/60) = 7/15. Remaining = 8/15. B fills this in (8/15) * 20 = 32/3 = 10 min 40 sec. Total = 4 + 10m 40s = 14m 40s.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'A is twice as good a workman as B and together they finish a piece of work in 18 days. In how many days will A alone finish the work?', 'option_a': '27', 'option_b': '54', 'option_c': '30', 'option_d': '36', 'correct_answer': 'A', 'explanation': 'Let B take 2x days, A takes x days. 1/x + 1/2x = 1/18 => 3/2x = 1/18 => 2x=54 => x=27.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'P can do a work in 15 days and Q in 20 days. If they work on it together for 4 days, then the fraction of the work that is left is:', 'option_a': '1/4', 'option_b': '1/10', 'option_c': '7/15', 'option_d': '8/15', 'correct_answer': 'D', 'explanation': 'Work done in 4 days = 4(1/15 + 1/20) = 4(7/60) = 7/15. Left = 1 - 7/15 = 8/15.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'A can lay railway track between two given stations in 16 days and B can do the same job in 12 days. With help of C, they did the job in 4 days only. Then, C alone can do the job in:', 'option_a': '9.6 days', 'option_b': '9.2 days', 'option_c': '10 days', 'option_d': '10.5 days', 'correct_answer': 'A', 'explanation': '1/16 + 1/12 + 1/C = 1/4 => 1/C = 1/4 - 7/48 = 5/48. C = 48/5 = 9.6 days.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'If 6 men and 8 boys can do a piece of work in 10 days while 26 men and 48 boys can do the same in 2 days, the time taken by 15 men and 20 boys in doing the same type of work will be:', 'option_a': '4 days', 'option_b': '5 days', 'option_c': '6 days', 'option_d': '7 days', 'correct_answer': 'A', 'explanation': '10(6M+8B) = 2(26M+48B) => 60M+80B = 52M+96B => 8M = 16B => 1M = 2B. Total work = 10(12B+8B) = 200B. 15M+20B = 50B. Time = 200/50 = 4 days.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'A tank is filled by three pipes with uniform flow. The first two pipes operating simultaneously fill the tank in the same time during which the tank is filled by the third pipe alone. The second pipe fills the tank 5 hours faster than the first pipe and 4 hours slower than the third pipe. The time required by the first pipe is:', 'option_a': '6 hours', 'option_b': '10 hours', 'option_c': '15 hours', 'option_d': '30 hours', 'correct_answer': 'C', 'explanation': 'Let third pipe = x hrs. Second = x+4. First = x+9. 1/(x+9) + 1/(x+4) = 1/x. Solving yields x = 6. First pipe = 6+9 = 15 hours.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'Three pipes A, B and C can fill a tank in 6 hours. After working at it together for 2 hours, C is closed and A and B can fill the remaining part in 7 hours. The number of hours taken by C alone to fill the tank is:', 'option_a': '10', 'option_b': '12', 'option_c': '14', 'option_d': '16', 'correct_answer': 'C', 'explanation': 'Part filled in 2 hrs = 2/6 = 1/3. Remaining = 2/3. A+B fill 2/3 in 7 hrs, so full in 21/2 hrs. C\'s 1 hr work = 1/6 - 2/21 = 1/14. So 14 hours.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},

            # --- Time, Speed & Distance, Trains, Boats ---
