            {'question_text': 'In how many ways can the letters of "APPLE" be arranged?', 'option_a': '60', 'option_b': '120', 'option_c': '24', 'option_d': '48', 'correct_answer': 'A', 'explanation': '5! / 2! (for two Ps) = 120 / 2 = 60.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'What is the probability of getting a sum of 9 from two throws of a dice?', 'option_a': '1/6', 'option_b': '1/8', 'option_c': '1/9', 'option_d': '1/12', 'correct_answer': 'C', 'explanation': 'Favorable outcomes: (3,6), (4,5), (5,4), (6,3). 4/36 = 1/9.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'From a group of 7 men and 6 women, 5 persons are to be selected to form a committee so that at least 3 men are there. In how many ways can it be done?', 'option_a': '564', 'option_b': '645', 'option_c': '735', 'option_d': '756', 'correct_answer': 'D', 'explanation': 'Cases: (3M,2W) or (4M,1W) or (5M,0W). Combinations = (7C3*6C2) + (7C4*6C1) + (7C5) = (35*15) + (35*6) + 21 = 525 + 210 + 21 = 756.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'Two cards are drawn together from a pack of 52 cards. The probability that one is a spade and one is a heart is:', 'option_a': '3/20', 'option_b': '29/34', 'option_c': '47/100', 'option_d': '13/102', 'correct_answer': 'D', 'explanation': 'P = (13C1 * 13C1) / 52C2 = (13 * 13) / ((52*51)/2) = 169 / 1326 = 13/102.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'Tickets numbered 1 to 20 are mixed up and then a ticket is drawn at random. What is the probability that the ticket drawn has a number which is a multiple of 3 or 5?', 'option_a': '1/2', 'option_b': '2/5', 'option_c': '8/15', 'option_d': '9/20', 'correct_answer': 'D', 'explanation': 'Multiples of 3: 3,6,9,12,15,18 (6). Multiples of 5: 5,10,15,20 (4). Multiples of both: 15 (1). Total = 6+4-1 = 9. Prob = 9/20.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'In how many different ways can the letters of the word \'OPTICAL\' be arranged so that the vowels always come together?', 'option_a': '120', 'option_b': '720', 'option_c': '4320', 'option_d': '2160', 'correct_answer': 'B', 'explanation': 'Vowels are O, I, A. Treat them as 1 unit. Total units = 4 consonants + 1 vowel unit = 5 units. Arrange units = 5!. Arrange vowels = 3!. Total = 120 * 6 = 720.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'In a box, there are 8 red, 7 blue and 6 green balls. One ball is picked up randomly. What is the probability that it is neither red nor green?', 'option_a': '1/3', 'option_b': '3/4', 'option_c': '7/19', 'option_d': '8/21', 'correct_answer': 'A', 'explanation': 'Total balls = 21. Neither red nor green means it must be blue. Prob = 7/21 = 1/3.', 'difficulty': 'easy'},
            {'question_text': 'Out of 7 consonants and 4 vowels, how many words of 3 consonants and 2 vowels can be formed?', 'option_a': '210', 'option_b': '1050', 'option_c': '25200', 'option_d': '21400', 'correct_answer': 'C', 'explanation': 'Select = 7C3 * 4C2 = 35 * 6 = 210. Arrange the 5 letters = 5!. Total = 210 * 120 = 25200.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'A bag contains 2 red, 3 green and 2 blue balls. Two balls are drawn at random. What is the probability that none of the balls drawn is blue?', 'option_a': '10/21', 'option_b': '11/21', 'option_c': '2/7', 'option_d': '5/7', 'correct_answer': 'A', 'explanation': 'Total balls = 7. Total ways = 7C2 = 21. Favorable (not blue, meaning from 5 remaining) = 5C2 = 10. Prob = 10/21.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'How many 3-digit numbers can be formed from the digits 2, 3, 5, 6, 7 and 9, which are divisible by 5 and none of the digits is repeated?', 'option_a': '5', 'option_b': '10', 'option_c': '15', 'option_d': '20', 'correct_answer': 'D', 'explanation': 'Number must end in 5. So unit place has 1 option. Remaining 2 places can be filled by remaining 5 digits in 5P2 ways = 5*4 = 20.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},

