            {'question_text': 'The length of a rectangle is halved, while its breadth is tripled. What is the percentage change in area?', 'option_a': '25% increase', 'option_b': '50% increase', 'option_c': '50% decrease', 'option_d': '75% increase', 'correct_answer': 'B', 'explanation': 'New Area = (L/2) * (3B) = 1.5 LB. Increase is 0.5 LB, which is 50%.', 'difficulty': 'easy'},
            {'question_text': 'If the radius of a circle is increased by 20%, its area increases by:', 'option_a': '20%', 'option_b': '40%', 'option_c': '44%', 'option_d': '46%', 'correct_answer': 'C', 'explanation': 'Area is proportional to r^2. 1.2 * 1.2 = 1.44. So 44% increase.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'A hollow iron pipe is 21 cm long and its external diameter is 8 cm. If the thickness of the pipe is 1 cm and iron weighs 8 g/cm3, then the weight of the pipe is:', 'option_a': '3.6 kg', 'option_b': '3.696 kg', 'option_c': '36 kg', 'option_d': '36.9 kg', 'correct_answer': 'B', 'explanation': 'External R=4, Internal r=3. Volume = pi*h*(R^2 - r^2) = (22/7)*21*(16-9) = 462 cm3. Weight = 462 * 8 = 3696 g = 3.696 kg.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'Today is Monday. After 61 days, it will be:', 'option_a': 'Tuesday', 'option_b': 'Wednesday', 'option_c': 'Thursday', 'option_d': 'Saturday', 'correct_answer': 'D', 'explanation': '61 / 7 leaves remainder 5. Monday + 5 days = Saturday.', 'difficulty': 'easy'},
            {'question_text': 'How many times do the hands of a clock coincide in a day?', 'option_a': '20', 'option_b': '21', 'option_c': '22', 'option_d': '24', 'correct_answer': 'C', 'explanation': 'They coincide 11 times in 12 hours. So, 22 times in 24 hours.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'What was the day of the week on 15th August, 1947?', 'option_a': 'Thursday', 'option_b': 'Friday', 'option_c': 'Saturday', 'option_d': 'Sunday', 'correct_answer': 'B', 'explanation': '1946 years = 1 odd day. Days in 1947 to Aug 15 = 227 days = 3 odd days. Total odd days = 4 = Thursday, plus leap year calculus makes it Friday. (Standard memorized fact).', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'A rectangular park 60 m long and 40 m wide has two concrete crossroads running in the middle of the park and rest of the park has been used as a lawn. If the area of the lawn is 2109 sq. m, then what is the width of the road?', 'option_a': '2.91 m', 'option_b': '3 m', 'option_c': '5.82 m', 'option_d': 'None', 'correct_answer': 'B', 'explanation': 'Area of lawn = (60-x)(40-x) = 2109. x^2 - 100x + 2400 = 2109 => x^2 - 100x + 291 = 0. Solving gives x=3 or 97. It cannot be 97, so 3.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'The surface area of a cube is 150 sq cm. Its volume is:', 'option_a': '64 cm3', 'option_b': '125 cm3', 'option_c': '150 cm3', 'option_d': '216 cm3', 'correct_answer': 'B', 'explanation': 'Surface area = 6a^2 = 150 => a^2 = 25 => a=5. Volume = a^3 = 125.', 'difficulty': 'easy'},
            
            # --- Extended Volume 1 (10 More Mixed Questions) ---
            {'question_text': 'Evaluate: (0.96 * 0.96 * 0.96 + 0.04 * 0.04 * 0.04) / (0.96 * 0.96 - 0.96 * 0.04 + 0.04 * 0.04)', 'option_a': '0.92', 'option_b': '1.0', 'option_c': '1.92', 'option_d': 'None', 'correct_answer': 'B', 'explanation': 'Formula: (a^3 + b^3) / (a^2 - ab + b^2) = a + b. So 0.96 + 0.04 = 1.0.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'If log 2 = 0.3010 and log 3 = 0.4771, the value of log 512 is:', 'option_a': '2.870', 'option_b': '2.967', 'option_c': '2.709', 'option_d': '3.876', 'correct_answer': 'C', 'explanation': 'log(512) = log(2^9) = 9 * log 2 = 9 * 0.3010 = 2.709.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'A trader gives a discount of 10% on the marked price of a watch. He still makes a profit of 20%. What is the ratio of CP to MP?', 'option_a': '3:4', 'option_b': '4:5', 'option_c': '5:6', 'option_d': '6:7', 'correct_answer': 'A', 'explanation': 'SP = 90% of MP. Also SP = 120% of CP. So 0.9 MP = 1.2 CP => CP/MP = 0.9/1.2 = 3/4.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'What is the sum of all two digit numbers divisible by 5?', 'option_a': '945', 'option_b': '950', 'option_c': '985', 'option_d': 'None', 'correct_answer': 'A', 'explanation': 'Sequence: 10, 15, ... 95. N = ((95-10)/5) + 1 = 18. Sum = (18/2)*(10+95) = 9*105 = 945.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'The difference between a two-digit number and the number obtained by interchanging the digits is 36. What is the difference between the sum and the difference of the digits of the number if the ratio between the digits is 1:2?', 'option_a': '4', 'option_b': '8', 'option_c': '16', 'option_d': 'None', 'correct_answer': 'B', 'explanation': 'Difference = 9(x-y) = 36 => x-y=4. Since ratio is 1:2, numbers are 4 and 8. Sum = 12, Diff = 4. Difference between them = 12-4=8.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'The value of a machine depreciates at 10% per annum. If its present value is Rs. 162,000, what was its value 2 years ago?', 'option_a': '200000', 'option_b': '190000', 'option_c': '180000', 'option_d': 'None', 'correct_answer': 'A', 'explanation': 'P * (0.9)^2 = 162000 => P * 0.81 = 162000 => P = 200000.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
            {'question_text': 'Two pipes can fill a tank in 20 and 24 mins respectively. A waste pipe can empty 3 gallons per minute. All three working together can fill tank in 15 mins. Capacity of tank is:', 'option_a': '60 gal', 'option_b': '100 gal', 'option_c': '120 gal', 'option_d': '150 gal', 'correct_answer': 'C', 'explanation': '1/20 + 1/24 - 1/C = 1/15. Solving gives C = 40 mins. Since it empties 3 gal/min, total = 40*3 = 120 gallons.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'A man sitting in a train which is traveling at 50 kmph observes that a goods train, traveling in opposite direction, takes 9 seconds to pass him. If the goods train is 280 m long, find its speed.', 'option_a': '58', 'option_b': '60', 'option_c': '62', 'option_d': '64', 'correct_answer': 'C', 'explanation': 'Relative speed = 280/9 m/s = (280/9)*(18/5) = 112 kmph. 112 = 50 + speed of goods train => 62 kmph.', 'difficulty': 'hard'},
            {'question_text': 'If 20% of a = b, then b% of 20 is the same as:', 'option_a': '4% of a', 'option_b': '5% of a', 'option_c': '20% of a', 'option_d': 'None', 'correct_answer': 'A', 'explanation': 'b = 0.2a. b% of 20 = (b/100)*20 = b/5. Substitute b: (0.2a)/5 = 0.04a = 4% of a.', 'difficulty': 'medium'},
